<sections><clause id="_87e3e027-e1fa-4d8c-a513-c842a3e42cb3" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative">

<p id="_6b43a27b-d7c8-4e6c-b23d-da88e7e12b2d">
<strong><sup>115</sup>In<sup>+</sup>, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn><msup><mrow><mtext>s</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>&#160;</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mtext>S</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>s</mtext><mn>5</mn><mtext>p</mtext><msup><mrow><mtext>&#160;</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math></stem> unperturbed optical transition</strong>
</p>
</clause>
<clause id="_recommended_value_of_the_frequency_in_the_cipm_list_of_frequencies" obligation="normative"><title>Recommended value <eref type="inline" bibitemid="cctf" citeas="[1]"/> of the frequency in the CIPM List of Frequencies</title><p id="_57a22b1c-abd9-4ad9-a861-614f5bd428fb">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>115</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>In</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>+</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1267402452901050</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_50e5bd0f-25c3-4798-8a22-12b9250f91e6">equivalent to</p>
<p id="_4bc1ca7c-dc6f-420c-9bb3-527758330d9b"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>115</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>In</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>+</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>236540853.549544</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>,</p>
<p id="_4e3a3bad-c891-40a9-ad12-651bc4f77723">with a relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1.6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>14</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>.</p></clause>
<clause id="_source_data" obligation="normative"><title>Source data</title><dl id="_5961761c-fd73-477c-9fe5-8b42f7be2b11">
<dt>Adopted value</dt>
<dd>
<p id="_c96cd3ad-c328-47c8-b009-0388421242a1">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>115</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>In</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>+</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1267402452901050</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</p>
</dd>
</dl>
<p id="_7a086569-3847-4a11-bf95-abecec23b287">with a relative uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1.6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>&#8722;</mi><mn>14</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem> calculated from</p>
<table id="_bdba5abc-7299-48c0-8571-85be61f3f0aa" unnumbered="true">
<thead>
<tr>
<th valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>115</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>In</mtext></mrow><mrow><mtext>+</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>/</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</th>
<th valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>u</mi><mo>/</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</th>
<th valign="top" align="left">source data</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1267402452899920</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>690</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left"><eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/><fn reference="a"><p id="_41383a77-bbe8-4851-9d86-100ee1e37ec7">From the least square procedure it turned out that the value and the uncertainty given in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/> is not compatible with the remaining data. Thus the uncertainty given in the original publication <eref type="inline" bibitemid="zanthier" citeas="[2]"/> was increased to <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>690</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem> to make it statistically more consistent.</p></fn></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1267402452901265</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>256</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<eref type="inline" bibitemid="wang_dumke" citeas="[3]"/>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1267402452901049.9</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>20.7</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="left"><eref type="inline" bibitemid="ohtsubo" citeas="[4]"/><fn reference="b"><p id="_3f0fbb25-287c-49d5-8dc3-c46d16d5ce2f">The uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>6.9</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem> presented in ref. <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ohtsubo" citeas="[4]"/> was increased by a factor of three because it dominates the result with its uncertainty much lower than any of the others. Another fourth measurement <eref type="inline" bibitemid="wang_liu" citeas="[5]"/> has not been used since the data were identical with the ones of ref. <eref type="inline" bibitemid="wang_dumke" citeas="[3]"/> but a much lower uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>63</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem> was reported without reasoning. The modification of the uncertainties followed the procedures outlined in ref. <eref type="inline" bibitemid="riehle" citeas="[6]"/>.</p></fn></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p id="_48aa6473-25cc-47fd-9381-c684bafb5e40">as a weighted mean of the above values.</p></clause>
